-- Blackhawks Defeat Rangers 4-2 to End Nine-Game Losing Streak in NHL
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2012-02-17T05:01:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-17/blackhawks-defeat-rangers-4-2-to-end-nine-game-losing-streak-in-nhl.html
The  Chicago Blackhawks  ended a nine-
game losing streak in the  National Hockey League  with a 4-2 win
against the Eastern Conference-leading New York Rangers.  Jonathan Toews, Nick Leddy,  Patrick Sharp  and Marian Hossa
gave the Blackhawks a 4-0 lead 10 minutes into the first period
last night at Madison Square Garden in New York.  Marc Staal scored in the second period and Carl Hagelin had
a goal in the third for the Rangers.  Corey Crawford had 22 saves for the Blackhawks and Martin Biron recorded 18 saves for the Rangers.  New York (37-14-5) has 79 points, one fewer than the
Detroit Red Wings (39-17-2), who have the best record in the
league. Chicago (30-21-7) is sixth in the Western Conference
with 67 points.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
